CI/CD Pipeline Design for EKS:
.gitlab-ci.yml:

stages:
  - build
  - push
  - deploy

variables:
  IMAGE_TAG: $CI_REGISTRY_IMAGE:$CI_COMMIT_TAG

build:
  stage: build
  script:
    - docker build -t $IMAGE_TAG .
  only:
    - tags

push:
  stage: push
  script:
    - docker login -u $CI_REGISTRY_USER -p $CI_REGISTRY_PASSWORD $CI_REGISTRY
    - docker push $IMAGE_TAG
  only:
    - tags

deploy:
  stage: deploy
  script:
    - aws eks update-kubeconfig --name wdtech-cluster --region us-east-1
    - kubectl set image deployment/wdtech-property-valuation wdtech-property-valuation=$IMAGE_TAG
  only:
    - tags

Kubernetes Deployment Manifest:
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: wdtech-property-valuation
spec:
  replicas: 2
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: wdtech-property-valuation
          image: registry.gitlab.com/wdtech/wdtech-property-valuation:1.0.0
          ports:
            - containerPort: 8000
          env:
            - name: BASE_PRICE_PER_SQFT
              value: "200"
            - name: APP_ENV
              value: "production"
```

**End-to-End Pipeline Flow:**
```
Developer pushes tag v1.0.0 to GitLab
        ↓
GitLab CI triggers automatically
        ↓
BUILD — docker build creates wdtech-property-valuation:1.0.0
        ↓
PUSH — image pushed to docker-registry.wdtech.org
        ↓
DEPLOY — kubectl updates EKS deployment with new image
        ↓
Kubernetes pulls image and rolls out 2 pods
        ↓
API live and serving requests
```

**Outcome:** Environment variables successfully injected and verified. CI/CD pipeline designed for full EKS deployment. ✅

